HEADWORD: Secularity
<hw>Sec`u*lar"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧cularit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, LL. <ets>saecularitas</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Supreme attention to the things of the present life;
worldliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>secularity</qex> of character which makes Christianity and
its principal doctrines distasteful or unintelligible.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

